# Project conventions

## Authority

`docs/design.md` is the single source of truth. Implement only what it specifies.

## Stack (fixed)

- Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- SQLite + Prisma (no Postgres)
- Zod validation, nanoid tokens, date-fns (JST)

## Product constraints

- No user login or accounts
- Access via unguessable URL tokens (`eventId`, `hostToken`, `responseToken`)
- Guest answers: `available` / `unavailable` only
- Timezone: JST for all date/time display and input
- UI copy in Japanese

## Code style

- Minimal diff; no scope creep
- Shared schemas in `src/lib/schemas.ts`
- API logic in `src/app/api/`; UI in `src/app/` and `src/components/`
- 404 for invalid IDs/tokens without leaking resource existence

## Agent roles

| Agent | Owns |
|-------|------|
| architect | Prisma, API, lib utilities |
| frontend | Pages, components, client UX |
| qa | Acceptance tests, README |

Do not commit unless the user asks.
